verses.roman:
svarūpa-gosāñi bhāla miṣṭa-prasāda lañā
prabhuke nivedana kare āge dāṇḍāñā

synonyms: svarūpa-gosāñi—Svarūpa Dāmodara; bhāla—first-class; miṣṭa-prasāda—sweetmeats; lañā—taking; prabhuke—unto Lord Caitanya Mahāprabhu; nivedana kare—offered; āge—in front of Him; dāṇḍāñā—standing.
translation: Svarūpa Dāmodara Gosvāmī then brought some excellent sweetmeats and, standing before the Lord, offered them to Him.
